h: Road accident deaths up in Vizag this year
sub_h: In 2022, the city of Vizag had 1327 Road accidents, compared to 1463 in 2021. The main reason for the increase in accidents in Vizag was that more people were on the roads. However, the city police department made efforts to mitigate the accidents, such as using speed laser guns and checking for drunk driving. In total, 333 people died in s in 2022, compared to 329 in 2021. The police also filed 8893 drunken driving cases in 2022, and of these 183 motorists were sent to jail. Over 1400 motorists were asked to campaign against drunken driving at important junctions for three days. The majority of the victims in road mishaps were two-wheeled riders, who were flouting traffic norms and engaging in accidents. The city police department is working to decrease the number of s by 10% in 2023.

sub_h: Four inmates were burnt alive when the SUV in which they were travelling rammed into a tipper near the Kadapa airport in the early hours on Monday.

h: Andhra Pradesh: Three killed, one injured in Road accident in Chittoor
sub_h: Three persons were killed on the spot, while one sustained grievous injuries in a gory Road accident in Chittoor district on Saturday.

h: Speed breakers, barricades bring down Road accidents
5, including 4 of a family, killed in Road accident
SUV rams into divider, two dead
Andhra Pradesh: Three dead, 15 injured in tractor mishap
sub_h: Two women and a seven-year-old kid died on the spot while 15 others suffered injuries after an over-crowded tractor lost control near Modalapalli village under Tavanapalli mandal in Chittoor district on Wednesday.

h: Stray cattle plague VZM roads, 228 dead in mishaps
Andhra Pradesh: Four killed in Kadapa road mishap
sub_h: Four persons were killed while four others sustained injuries in a Road accident involving a truck and an SUV near Bandapalle in Ramapuram Mandal of Andhra Pradesh's Kadapa district on Wednesday.

h: Andhra Pradesh: Woman, baby killed in Road accident at Chandragiri
sub_h: A 32-year-old woman and her 13-month-old daughter were killed after the bike she was riding pillion was hit by a speeding tractor near Chandragiri in Chittoor district on Sunday.

h: Visakhapatnam: Two dead, 3 injured in bike-auto collision
sub_h: Two persons died on the spot and three others sustained injuries following collision between an auto-rickshaw, carrying five passengers, and a bike on the outskirts of Bennavaram village on Wednesday.

h: Chittoor: 3 killed in separate Road accidents
sub_h: Three persons including a trainee sub inspector were killed in three separate Road accidents in Chittoor and Kurnool districts on Sunday
